        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:13PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 3 miles southeast of Preston to 2 miles east of
Calvin. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 40 to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arpelar...                        Beggs...
Preston...                        Raiford...
Weleetka...                       Dewar...
Haywood...                        Hanna...
Pierce...                         Clearview...
Schulter...                       Eram...
Morris...                         Pharoah...
Grayson...                        Ashland...
Bryant...                         Hoffman...
Okmulgee...                       Hitchita...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 223 and
253.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
